editorialNotes.tagline: New ways to sketch and animate
editorialNotes.standard: Procreate lets you generate high-caliber artwork at a blistering pace using a robust layering system, stunning filters, and thousands of importable brushes. Plus, Savage Interactive’s super-intuitive app supports pressure sensitivity and Apple Pencil—as well as iCloud Drive and a seamless video recording of each brushstroke—so sharing your work is incredibly simple.
editorialNotes.short: This super-intuitive app makes it simple to paint your next masterpiece.
Learn to read and pronounce words with your new friend!
editorialNotes.tagline: Learn to read with a friend

ios.subtitle: Install all the fonts you love

editorialNotes.standard: Wherever you are on your filmmaking journey, LumaFusion meets you there. This multitrack video editor offers pros the features rarely found in an iPad app, all accessible through an intuitive touch interface that even beginners can get the hang of.
editorialNotes.short: Apply transitions, effects and more with these powerful editing tools.

editorialNotes.tagline: The tools for your first draft

editorialNotes.short: Try a wild new look – risk-free!

editorialNotes.standard: Everyone needs a task manager—and Things is adaptable enough for anyone. This Apple Design Award winner is crisp and lightweight, featuring a simple but effective interface. The ever-present Magic Plus button makes it easy to add to-dos from anywhere in the app, and organizing items is as simple as dragging them where you want them. It’s like the unicorn of productivity tools: deep enough for serious work, surprisingly easy to use, and gorgeous enough to enjoy staring at.
editorialNotes.short: Organise class projects, assignments and daily to-do lists.

editorialNotes.standard: Nothing beats a kid-friendly game that keeps the whole family captivated—and Toca has us snipping, straightening, and styling to our heart's content. Once we've perfected our customer's silly new ‘dos, we make sure to add some accessories, snap a pic, and share the hair.

Learning the ABCs is child's play with this entertaining and educational app. Adorable artwork, colorful creatures, and smooth voice and sound effects enhance an already engaging hands-on experience that makes spelling each and every word an interactive puzzle.

Pixelmator sets a new standard for photo editing on iPhone and iPad with a suite of staggeringly powerful tools. Combining gorgeous templates, intuitive touch-screen controls, and completely customizable effects, this full-featured editor is in a class all its own. Plus, with seamless syncing using iCloud Drive, it doesn’t matter where the project was started—you can keep editing on your iPhone, iPad, or Mac.
editorialNotes.short: Make your pictures shine with this professional set of photography tools.

editorialNotes.standard: The moment we met wee kitty Crumbs in Little Kitten, we let out an audible “awww.” This adorable digital feline encourages children to play and explore, interacting with the lively toys and simple games in Crumbs’ room. We’re amazed by the cinematic animation, and appreciate the sleep timer that sends Crumbs to bed when our kids’ screen time is over.
editorialNotes.short: Embark on exciting adventures with your own kitty pal.

ios.subtitle: A place to start musical ideas

name: Don't Let Pigeon Run This App!
e-Sword HD: Bible Study to Go

ios.subtitle: Study the Bible fast and easy!

editorialNotes.standard: When we want to hunker down and type without distraction, one of our favorite resources is iA Writer. Substantially updated since its initial release, this writing app offers a customizable keyboard, selective text highlighting, iCloud sync, and many other features we’ve come to depend on. Plus, a streamlined interface lets you simply swipe left to preview a document and swipe right to access your library. The entire experience is designed to be quick and easy so you can focus on your work.
editorialNotes.short: A streamlined interface with a customisable keyboard, iCloud sync and more.

ios.subtitle: The fun way to learn to write

editorialNotes.standard: In this imaginative animated storybook, two of Sesame Street’s most popular characters team up to spark your child’s love of reading. As fearful Grover concocts hilarious obstacles to keep kids from reaching the last page, eager Elmo asks for their help to discover the mysterious monster at the end of the story. It’s an engaging experience that teaches bravery and conflict resolution through lively interactivity, adorable artwork, and heartwarming humor. Parental tips help you integrate these lessons during storytime and beyond, combining learning and play with practical advice from a name you can trust.

editorialNotes.short: Help yourself resist distractions from your device.
Join Grover as he tries to keep you away from the monster at the end of this book!
